column1: About the data: Voter demographics per state. Source: http://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2016-swing-the-election/
Voter turnout was set to 100% to get the correct demographics
1. Used the import_table.py script to extract the table, saved to demographics.csv
2. Converted pop.json to CSV using http://www.convertcsv.com/json-to-csv.htm
3. Merged the CSVs from step1 and 2 to get this table
4. renamed column headers for CSV in step 1 to merge with pop.json
5. converted merged CSV back to json using http://www.convertcsv.com/csv-to-json.htm
6. saved the new json as pop_new.json
